{
    "title": "Learning Streaming Video Representation via Multitask Training",
    "authors": [
        "Yibin Yan",
        "Jilan Xu",
        "Shangzhe Di",
        "Yikun Liu",
        "Yudi Shi",
        "Qirui Chen",
        "Zeqian Li",
        "Yifei Huang",
        "Weidi Xie"
    ],
    "abstract": "Understanding continuous video streams plays a fundamental role in real-time applications, including embodied AI and autonomous driving. Unlike offline video processing, streaming video understanding requires the ability to process video streams frame by frame, preserve historical information, and make low-latency decisions. To address these challenges, our main contributions are three-fold. (i) we develop a novel streaming video backbone, termed as StreamFormer, by incorporating causal temporal attention into a pre-trained vision transformer. This enables efficient streaming video processing while maintaining image representation capability. (ii) to train StreamFormer, we propose to unify diverse spatial-temporal video understanding tasks within a multitask visual-language alignment framework. Hence, StreamFormer learns global semantics, temporal dynamics, and fine-grained spatial relationships simultaneously. (iii) we conduct extensive experiments for online action detection, online video instance segmentation, and video question answering. StreamFormer achieves competitive performance while maintaining efficiency, demonstrating its potential for real-time applications.",
    "summary": "本文提出了一种名为StreamFormer的新型流式视频骨干网络，通过在预训练视觉Transformer中引入因果时序注意力机制，实现了高效的帧级流式视频处理。为了训练该网络，作者设计了一个多任务视觉-语言对齐框架，统一了全局语义、时间动态和细粒度空间关系的学习目标。在在线动作检测、在线视频实例分割和视频问答等多个下游任务上的实验表明，StreamFormer在保持高效率的同时取得了具有竞争力的性能，展示了其在实时应用中的潜力。",
    "keywords": [
        "Streaming Video Understanding",
        "Causal Temporal Attention",
        "Multitask Learning",
        "Vision Transformer",
        "Visual-Language Alignment",
        "Online Action Detection",
        "Video Instance Segmentation",
        "Video Question Answering"
    ],
    "contributions": [
        "提出了StreamFormer，通过时序因果注意力和空间低秩适应，将预训练图像骨干网络有效转化为流式视频模型，在保持空间表示质量的同时实现高效流式视频处理。",
        "引入了一种分层多任务学习范式，系统性地统一了全局级、时序级和空间级的学习目标，使模型能够同时理解流式视频中的全局语义、时间动态和细粒度空间关系。",
        "在在线动作检测、在线视频实例分割和视频问答等多个下游任务上进行了大量实验，验证了该方法在流式场景中有效平衡了准确性和计算效率。"
    ],
    "limitations": [
        "论文主要关注于将预训练图像骨干网络改造为流式视频模型，对于从头开始训练或使用纯视频预训练权重的场景未进行深入探讨。",
        "多任务训练依赖于现有视频数据集中的细粒度人工标注（如像素级分割掩码），这些标注的获取成本较高，可能限制了方法在缺乏此类标注的新任务上的可扩展性。",
        "虽然实验展示了在多个任务上的有效性，但论文未详细分析模型在极端长视频或复杂场景（如严重遮挡、快速运动）下的性能退化情况。"
    ],
